abstract: In a major shift, the Democratic National Committee will eliminate the requirement that candidates to show evidence of grass-roots support.
snippet: In a major shift, the Democratic National Committee will eliminate the requirement that candidates to show evidence of grass-roots support.
lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — The Democratic National Committee has opened the door to allowing former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg of New York to participate in the presidential debate it will sponsor in Nevada next month, a change from its practice that demanded candidates demonstrate grass-roots fund-raising support.

headline_main: D.N.C. Rules Change for Nevada Debate Could Open Door for Bloomberg
headline_print_headline: Rule Change for Democrats’ Next Debate Opens Door for Bloomberg to Participate
byline_original: By Reid J. Epstein and Matt Stevens

abstract: The Democratic National Committee has dropped grassroots fundraising qualifications for the party’s Feb. 19 debate before the Nevada caucuses, opening the possibility that billionaire Michael Bloomberg could make his first appearance on stage.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee has dropped grassroots fundraising qualifications for the party’s Feb. 19 debate before the Nevada caucuses, opening the possibility that billionaire Michael Bloomberg could make his first appearance on stage.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — The Democratic National Committee has dropped grassroots fundraising qualifications for the party’s Feb. 19 debate before the Nevada caucuses, opening the possibility that billionaire Michael Bloomberg could make his first appearance on stage.
headline_main: Bloomberg Could Qualify for Debates Under New Party Rules
headline_print_headline: Bloomberg Could Qualify for Debates Under New Party Rules

abstract: The millennial former mayor of a midsize city has far surpassed expectations in the 2020 race. He doesn’t get fired up. Can he fire up people in Iowa?
snippet: The millennial former mayor of a midsize city has far surpassed expectations in the 2020 race. He doesn’t get fired up. Can he fire up people in Iowa?
lead_paragraph: OTTUMWA, Iowa — No presidential campaign is spared its awkward moments: overlong hugs from supporters, groaners about the Iowa weather, white lies about the caliber of the local cuisine.

abstract: In Michael Zapata’s debut novel, “The Lost Book of Adana Moreau,” an unfinished sci-fi manuscript bridges multiple universes, cosmic and human.
snippet: In Michael Zapata’s debut novel, “The Lost Book of Adana Moreau,” an unfinished sci-fi manuscript bridges multiple universes, cosmic and human.
lead_paragraph: Suppose that we live in a universe without “ifs.” What appears to be chance, or choice, is actually a peek into the rules of a completely separate universe that we can never access. Here, all our hopes for what might have been or what could be are accounted for; every outcome is settled, and we must play it as it lays.

headline_main: Generations of Exiles Collide in Post-Katrina New Orleans

abstract: Offill’s melancholy and satirical new novel is narrated by a woman who worries about everything from her troubled brother to climate change.
snippet: Offill’s melancholy and satirical new novel is narrated by a woman who worries about everything from her troubled brother to climate change.
lead_paragraph: My wife refuses to use Lyft or Uber in Manhattan because she thinks they’re evil. She thinks I’m a moral cretin for liking both so much. We don’t agree to disagree. We fight it out every time we step outside.

abstract: Spanish bank BBVA booked a loss of 155 million euros (£130 million) in the fourth quarter due to impairments in its U.S. business, while a modest increase in overall lending income belied the struggle with low interest rates for lenders across Spain.
snippet: Spanish bank BBVA booked a loss of 155 million euros (£130 million) in the fourth quarter due to impairments in its U.S. business, while a modest increase in overall lending income belied the struggle with low interest rates for lenders across Spa...
lead_paragraph: MADRID — Spanish bank BBVA booked a loss of 155 million euros (£130 million) in the fourth quarter due to impairments in its U.S. business, while a modest increase in overall lending income belied the struggle with low interest rates for lenders across Spain.
headline_main: Spain's BBVA Books $172 Million Quarterly Loss, Spanish Lenders' NII Pressured
headline_print_headline: Spain's BBVA Books $172 Million Quarterly Loss, Spanish Lenders' NII Pressured

abstract: Commonwealth Bank of Australia grew its home lending business in the second half of last year, the only one to do so of the four major banks, data showed on Friday, as offshore lenders lured customers with quick approvals and cheap money.
snippet: Commonwealth Bank of Australia grew its home lending business in the second half of last year, the only one to do so of the four major banks, data showed on Friday, as offshore lenders lured customers with quick approvals and cheap money.
lead_paragraph: SYDNEY — Commonwealth Bank of Australia grew its home lending business in the second half of last year, the only one to do so of the four major banks, data showed on Friday, as offshore lenders lured customers with quick approvals and cheap money.
headline_main: Australia's CBA, Big Offshore Banks Grow Home Lending Business
headline_print_headline: Australia's CBA, Big Offshore Banks Grow Home Lending Business

abstract: If Tinder is about your first impression, working on a cruise ship is about your 15th impression, or 29th.
snippet: If Tinder is about your first impression, working on a cruise ship is about your 15th impression, or 29th.
lead_paragraph: Among the many nicknames Erik had for me, my least favorite was Tinder. He had picked it not only because it rhymed with my last name, but also because, as he knew, I had done a lot of online dating before fleeing to take this job on a cruise ship.
